<TITLE>Chivas Guadalajara, Club America nab key wins on Liga MX matchday four</TITLE>
<TEXT>
Miguel Angel Samudio helped Club America to a 1-0 win over Veracruz. 
Week 4 in the 2017 Liga MX Clausura brought victories for Chivas and Club America, while Monterrey continues to struggle. 
 
Here's a look at the biggest talking points of the weekend: 
 
1. Chivas, America return to winning ways 
 
Whenever Mexico's two biggest teams lose a game, there is a certain amount of pressure, but both Club America and Chivas followed up defeats last weekend by picking up wins on Saturday. 
 
Las Aguilas started the round of matches in last place in the Clausura 2017 table with question starting to be asked about coach Ricardo La Volpe's future. 
 
It was recent signing Paraguayan Cecilio Dominguez who impressed the Estadio Azteca crowd on his debut, netting the winner against Veracruz in the 61st minute with a diving header after a neat move. 
 
This was a game America had to win. Goalkeeper Agustin Marchesin had leaked eight goals in his first three games of the year and had looked slightly nervous, but the clean sheet and three points should steady Las Aguilas moving forward. 
 
Over in Queretaro, Chivas earned a 1-0 against Gallos Blancos thanks to a first half goal from Jesus "Chapo" Sanchez, following an exquisite through-pass from Orbelin Pineda. 
 
It was a fully deserved victory for Guadalajara, with Queretaro was once again disappointing. Gallos Blancos have now gone 360 minutes without scoring a goal and Victor Manuel Vucetich will be worried about his team's lack of punch. 
  
